.Dd April 10, 2026
.Dt MOXY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moxy
.Nd MCP proxy that aggregates child MCP servers
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm serve mcp
.Nm
.Cm serve-http
.Op Fl -listen Ar addr
.Op Fl -expose Ar selector
.Nm
.Cm validate
.Nm
.Cm add
.Op Ar path
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
spawns child MCP servers as subprocesses, communicates with them via
JSON-RPC over stdio, and presents their tools, resources, and prompts
through a single unified MCP server.
Child server capabilities are namespaced with a dot separator
.Pq e.g. grit.status, folio.read .
.Pp
Configuration is loaded from a hierarchy of TOML moxyfiles
.Pq see Xr moxyfile 5
and declarative tool configs (moxins) discovered from
.Ev MOXIN_PATH
.Pq see Xr moxin 7 .
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width "serve-http"
.It Cm serve mcp
Run as an MCP proxy server over stdio.
This is the default command when invoked via the MCP protocol.
Loads the moxyfile hierarchy, spawns child MCP servers, performs
initialize handshakes, probes ephemeral servers, discovers moxins from
.Ev MOXIN_PATH ,
and serves as a unified MCP server on stdin/stdout.
Shuts down gracefully on
.Dv SIGINT .
.It Cm serve-http Op Fl -listen Ar addr Op Fl -expose Ar selector Op Fl -name-template Ar template
Run as an MCP proxy server over streamable HTTP, serving
.Pa /healthz ,
.Pa /mcp ,
and
.Pa /clown/system-prompt
(a dynamic system-prompt fragment clown fetches once at session launch,
reflecting live child-server state \(em connected servers with tool counts
and any that failed to start; 204 when there is nothing to add).
With no
.Fl -listen
flag, binds an ephemeral port on
.Li 127.0.0.1
and prints a clown-plugin-protocol handshake line to stdout, for use
under a clown-plugin-host.
With
.Fl -listen Ar addr
.Pq e.g. Li 127.0.0.1:8731 ,
binds that fixed address instead, suppresses the handshake line, and
logs the bound address to stderr only \(em use this to place
.Nm
behind a reverse proxy or tunnel that needs a stable upstream.
The
.Ev MOXY_HTTP_ADDR
environment variable applies the same fixed-bind behavior to the default
.Pq stdio
command.
.Pp
The
.Fl -expose Ar selector
flag restricts which categories of tools are advertised and dispatched \(em
for strict or public frontends that should not see moxy's full surface.
Every tool is classified by name into one of three categories:
.Sy child
.Pq proxied child-server tools, e.g. grit.status ,
.Sy resource-bridge
.Pq synthetic <server>.resource-read / .resource-templates tools ,
and
.Sy meta
.Pq moxy and framework builtins: status, restart, batch, async\(emfamily .
.Ar selector
is a comma-separated list applied left-to-right over a base of
.Sy full :
a profile name
.Pq Sy full , Sy no-meta , Sy resources-only
resets the set, and a
.Sy + Ns Ar cat
/
.Sy - Ns Ar cat
toggle adjusts it
.Pq e.g. Li -meta , Li resources-only .
An excluded category is neither listed nor callable, so
.Li --expose resources-only
on a public origin exposes children's resources natively while hiding all
tools, and
.Li --expose no-meta
keeps child tools but removes moxy's control surface.
Resources are served natively regardless of this flag.
Omitting it
.Pq or Li --expose full
exposes everything, the default.
Unknown profile or category names are rejected at startup.
See docs/features/0006-tool-exposure-filter.md.
.Pp
The
.Fl -name-template Ar template
flag changes how child tool and prompt names are advertised. The default
.Pq Li "{server}.{tool}"
is the historical dot join; a strict frontend such as claude.ai rejects any
tool name containing a dot, so
.Li "--name-template '{server}_{tool}'"
advertises dot-free names
.Pq e.g. Li grit_commit
that pass its
.Li ^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]{1,64}$
validator.
.Ar template
is arbitrary text with the placeholders
.Li {server}
and
.Li {tool} ;
.Li {tool}
is required, while
.Li {server}
is optional
.Pq dropping it , e.g. Li "{tool}" , risks cross-server collisions .
A malformed template is rejected at flag parse; a template under which two
distinct
.Pq server, tool
pairs render to the same name is rejected at startup rather than silently
shadowing one. Dispatch reverse-resolves a rendered name through a registry
built at list time, so it round-trips to the child's original tool regardless of
template. The flag applies to
.Cm serve-http
only;
.Cm serve-mcp
always uses the default template.
.Pp
.Fl -name-template
is orthogonal to
.Fl -expose :
it changes how names are rendered, not which categories are exposed. It does
.Em not
hide moxy's control surface, and an empty
.Fl -expose
resolves to
.Sy full ,
so a public origin must still pass
.Fl -expose
to gate the meta tools \(em e.g.
.Li "--name-template '{server}_{tool}' --expose no-meta,-resource-bridge" ,
not name-template alone. See
.Cm render
below and docs/features/0007-name-template.md.
.It Cm render Op Fl -name-template Ar template
Render or reverse-resolve a namespaced tool/prompt name under a template,
without a running server. Forward
.Pq Fl -server Ar s Fl -tool Ar t
prints the advertised name; reverse
.Pq Fl -resolve Ar name
prints the canonical tab-separated
.Ar server No and Ar tool
via a structural inverse, which works only for invertible templates
.Pq exactly one Li {server} and one Li {tool} separated by a literal .
.Nm Cm render
does not introspect a running server \(em pass the same
.Fl -name-template
you gave
.Cm serve-http .
See docs/features/0007-name-template.md.
.It Cm validate
Validate the moxyfile hierarchy and output results in TAP version 14
format.
Checks TOML syntax, validates server names and commands, and verifies
executables exist on
.Ev PATH .
.It Cm add Op Ar path
Interactively add a server to a moxyfile using a terminal form.
The optional
.Ar path
argument specifies which moxyfile to modify; defaults to
.Pa moxyfile
in the current directory.
.El
.Sh NAMESPACING
Tools and prompts from child servers are namespaced as
.Ar server Ns Li \&. Ns Ar name
.Pq e.g. grit.status .
The dot separator is unambiguous because server names must not contain
dots.
.Pp
Resources and resource templates use a slash separator:
.Ar server Ns Li / Ns Ar uri .
.Sh META TOOLS
.Nm
injects two built-in tools into the unified server:
.Bl -tag -width "exec-mcp"
.It restart
Restart a configured child server or moxin by name.
For persistent servers, closes and re-spawns the process.
For ephemeral servers, re-probes capabilities.
For moxins, re-discovers the moxin's TOML from
.Ev MOXIN_PATH
and rebuilds the in-process server.
.Pp
Omit
.Li server
to reload everything: re-read the moxyfile hierarchy and
.Ev MOXIN_PATH ,
close every running child, re-spawn subprocess servers, rebuild moxin
servers, re-probe ephemeral, and emit one
.Li tools/list_changed .
.Pp
Annotated with
.Li destructiveHint: true ;
clients prompt the user before each invocation.
Claude Code does not propagate
.Li tools/list_changed
to the active conversation's system prompt \(em see
.Xr moxy-restart 7
for the workaround
.Pq /mcp \(-> Reconnect .
.It exec-mcp
Invoke a tool on a named child server directly, bypassing the
normal namespaced dispatch.
.El
.Sh DISCOVERY RESOURCES
.Nm
provides built-in resources for agent discovery:
.Bl -tag -width "moxy://tools/{server}/{tool}"
.It Li moxy://servers
JSON array of all child servers with capability counts and status.
.It Li moxy://servers/{server}
Details for a single child server.
.It Li moxy://tools/{server}
Tool names and descriptions for a child server.
.It Li moxy://tools/{server}/{tool}
Full JSON schema for a specific tool.
.El
.Pp
Unknown resource reads return structured JSON hints pointing to
.Li moxy://servers
instead of raw error messages.
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "CLAUDE_SESSION_ID"
.It Ev HOME
Used as the root for the configuration hierarchy walk.
.It Ev CLAUDE_SESSION_ID
Session identifier for native server result caching.
Checked first in the fallback chain; see
.Ev SPINCLASS_SESSION_ID .
.It Ev SPINCLASS_SESSION_ID
Session identifier set by
.Xr spinclass 1
in worktree sessions.
Used when
.Ev CLAUDE_SESSION_ID
is unset.
If neither is set, a UUID is generated per
.Nm
process.
.It Ev MOXIN_PATH
Colon-separated list of directories to search for moxin configs.
See
.Xr moxin 7
for discovery details.
.It Ev MOXY_HTTP_ADDR
When set on the default
.Pq stdio
command, serves streamable HTTP on the given fixed address
.Pq e.g. Li 127.0.0.1:8731
instead of stdio.
The
.Cm serve-http Fl -listen
flag is the first-class equivalent for the HTTP command.
.It Ev MOXY_CHILD_MAX_MESSAGE
Maximum size of a single newline-delimited JSON-RPC message
.Nm
will buffer from a child server's stdout before rejecting the line as an
oversize fault.
Accepts a raw byte count
.Pq e.g. Li 67108864
or a value with a unit suffix
.Pq e.g. Li 64MB , Li 256MiB , Li 1G .
Defaults to 64 MiB.
A child that emits a larger single line has that one message refused with a
self-diagnosing error naming this variable; the child keeps running and later
calls still work.
An unparseable or non-positive value falls back to the default.
.It Ev MOXY_CHILD_SPILL_OVERSIZE
When truthy
.Pq Li 1 , Li true , Li yes , No or Li on ,
spill an oversize child stdout line to a temporary file under
.Pa $TMPDIR/moxy/oversize/
while draining it, for post-mortem inspection or manual recovery.
Off by default.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "./.madder/local/share/blob_stores/default/"
.It Pa ~/.config/moxy/moxyfile
Global moxyfile.
.It Pa ./moxyfile
Project-local moxyfile.
.It Pa ~/.config/moxy/moxins/
Global moxin configs.
.It Pa ./.moxy/moxins/
Project-local moxin configs.
.It Pa ./.madder/local/share/blob_stores/default/
Per-repo
.Xr madder 1
blob store backing cached tool outputs from moxins.
Required at startup;
.Xr spinclass 1
auto-initializes one per worktree, otherwise run
.Sy madder init .default
from the repo root.
.It Pa $XDG_LOG_HOME/moxy/hooks/
Per-session hook event logs.
See
.Xr moxy-hooks 5 .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr moxin 7 ,
.Xr moxy-hooks 5 ,
.Xr moxy-restart 7 ,
.Xr moxyfile 5
